templates.mailtemp:
PROBLEM: Partitioner TOOL doesn't support "enum"s
SOLUTION: Will be supplied by DT's in next Q
WORK-AROUND:
Instead of 
typedef enum node { A = 1'b0, B = 1'b1 } t_enum_x;  
Please use the next type definiton: 
`ifdef INST_ON 
      typedef enum node { A = 1'b0, B = 1'b1 } t_enum_x; 
`else 
      typedef enum node { A = 1'b0, B = 1'b1 } t_enum; 
      typedef union packed { 
                  reg f1; 
                  t_enum f2; 
      } t_enum_x; 
`endif  

When running synthesis the union will be defined, that includes ENUM and it will create a proper Netlist.

PEREVENTIVE ACTION comment:
Fixing the bug in Partitioner Tool.

